Cut the bread with a flower-shaped cookie cutter. Then, spread the 8 flowers with margarine.

Cut the Emmental slices with a smaller flower-shaped cookie cutter.

Make sandwiches : take a bread flower and add Emmental cheese, fresh spinach shoots and close the sandwiches.

Put the sandwiches into your kidsâ€™ MB Tresor bento box and decorate with fresh spinach shoots and carrots slides.

The slices of bread can be toasted and used as croutons in a soup with the pieces of cheese and spinach pieces added to a salad.

The little trick:

Add a little ham or cream cheese!

For the 2 food cups :

Peel the carrot and cut it into sticks to make it easy to eat. Place the pieces in a food cup.

Peel the clementine and to place it in the second box with a madeleine cake.

